title: Authors
publication_title: James Ensor: The Temptation of Saint Anthony
content:
<section class="osci-tk-epub-section body" id="body">Susan M. Canning (SMC) is professor of art history at the College of New Rochelle in New York.

Patrick Florizoone (PF) is director of the James Ensor Archive, Ghent.

Nancy Ireson (NI) is Rothman Family Associate Curator in the Department of Prints and Drawings at the Art Institute of Chicago.

Kimberly J. Nichols (KJN) is associate paper conservator in the Department of Prints and Drawings at the Art Institute of Chicago.

Sabine Taevernier (ST) is an independent art historian in charge of the Ensor Advisory Committee.

Herwig Todts (HT) is curator of modern art at the Royal Museum of Fine Arts, Antwerp.

Debora Silverman (DS) is professor of history and art history at the University of California, Los Angeles.

Anna Swinbourne (AS) is an independent art historian.

</section>
